{"questionId":"27198","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A cafe makes <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> litres of coffee each morning. The cafe’s profit each morning, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math>, measured in dollars, is modelled by the following equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> is a positive constant.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an expression for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to expand given expression&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>1000</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>1000</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong> </em>for power rule correctly applied to at least one term and <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for correct answer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27198","referenceCode":"22M.2.SL.TZ2.5a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an expression for dCdx in terms of k and x.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}